# Documentation and Comments Rules

## Language Requirements
- All docstrings must be written in English
- All code comments must be written in English
- Use clear, descriptive English for all documentation
- **All Project Rules files (*.mdc) must be written in English**

## Project Rules Files (*.mdc)
- All Project Rules files must be written in English
- Use clear, descriptive language for rule definitions
- Follow consistent formatting and structure
- Include examples when helpful for clarity
- Maintain professional and technical writing standards

## General Documentation Standards
- Write self-documenting code with clear variable and function names
- Add comments for complex logic or business rules
- Keep documentation up to date with code changes
- Use consistent formatting and style across all documentation

